            "heading": "AWS Services Cheat Sheet",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "| AWS Service | Real World Equivalent | Use this to |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| EC2 | Virtual Servers | Host compute instances |\n| IAM | Identity Management | Control users, roles, and policies |\n| S3 | Unlimited Storage | Store files and objects |\n| VPC | Virtual Network | Isolated network infrastructure |\n| Lambda | Serverless Functions | Run code without servers |\n| API Gateway | API Proxy | Throttle and clean API requests |\n| RDS | Managed Database | SQL database hosting |\n| Route53 | DNS Service | Domain name management |\n| SES | Transactional Email | Send one-off notifications |\n| Cloudfront | CDN | Faster content delivery |\n| DynamoDB | NoSQL Database | Scalable key-value store |\n| Cognito | Auth as a Service | User identity management |\n| SQS | Queue Service | Store data for future processing |"
        },
